From 0824a44ca7394cbe88c0f06053858e2163f78dd8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 03:31:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Re-push full history when the relay's remote DB is rebuilt
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A redeploy on Render's ephemeral disk wipes the hosted archive DB, but
the Pi's relay cursor still said everything had been sent, so the old
archive days never came back. /api/ingest now returns a per-database
instance id, the pusher heartbeats every cycle (empty batches included),
and when the id changes it resets its cursor and re-sends the full
channel history — the receiver's dedupe absorbs any overlap.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PvmmS4BkYeVEQHmzcxE9ic
